(427, 'Agnès Varda', '1928-05-30', 'Brussels, Belgium', 1, 'https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/zfStaPgZo9aAHUH4sntmnpRcldd.jpg', 'Agnès Varda (born 30 May 1928) is a French film director and professor at the European Graduate School. Her movies, photographs, and art installations focus on documentary realism, feminist issues, and social commentary — with a distinct experimental style.\n\nDescription above from the Wikipedia article Agnès Varda, licensed under CC-BY-SA, full list of contributors on Wikipedia.'),
